{#
  Kill-active banner — Plan 02-05 Task 2 / UI-SPEC §2c.

  Appears when ``request.state.kill_active`` is True. Stacked BELOW the
  live/paper banner (z-index 49 vs 50). ARIA assertive — kill-active is
  the highest-stakes state and interrupts screen-reader queue.

  Two copy variants:
   * "boot-restored" — shown when kill_active_since indicates the kill was
     restored from a prior process restart (UI-SPEC §"Banner & Section Headers").
   * default — shown after an in-process kill, includes the n_cancelled/n_total
     tally when available.

  This template is also returned as the HTMX response body when POST /kill
  succeeds, swapping into the empty #kill-banner-mount placeholder.
#}
<div id="kill-banner-mount">
  <div class="banner-kill"
       role="alert"
       aria-live="assertive"
       aria-atomic="true">
    {% if boot_restored %}
      🚫 KILL ACTIVE — restored from previous session. UNKILL to resume.
    {% elif n_total is defined and n_cancelled is defined %}
      🚫 KILL ACTIVE — no orders will fire. Cancelled {{ n_cancelled }}/{{ n_total }} open orders.
    {% else %}
      🚫 KILL ACTIVE — no orders will fire.
    {% endif %}
    <button class="btn-kill"
            hx-get="/unkill/confirm-modal"
            hx-target="#modal-mount"
            hx-swap="innerHTML"
            aria-label="Open unkill confirmation. Resumes all trading."
            style="margin-left: 16px;">
      UNKILL
    </button>
  </div>
</div>
